The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network (CNN) framework for classification of electroencephalogram (EEG)-derived brain connectome in schizophrenia (SZ). The paper involves the use of deep learning methods and focuses on classification tasks, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
